{"formatVersion":"1","manifest":{"sourceId":"vivekanandaWisdom","displayName":"Swami Vivekananda","version":"1.0","language":"English","edition":"Wikiquote Verified","primaryCategory":"Philosophy & Spirituality","subcategory":"Vedanta","type":"quotes","browseOrder":"sequence","supportsRandom":true,"supportsBrowse":true,"groupingLevels":[],"sortPriority":40,"languageCode":"en","displayNameEnglish":"Swami Vivekananda","script":"Latin","isRTL":false,"transliterationAvailable":false,"contentRating":"devotional","audienceTags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","theme:philosophy","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"itemCount":226,"dataPath":"Data/Collections/Vivekananda_Wisdom.json"},"data":[{"id":"vivekananda-0001","text":"To succeed, you must have tremendous perseverance, tremendous will. “I will drink the ocean”, says the persevering soul; “at my will mountains will crumble up”. Have that sort of energy, that sort of will; work hard, and you will reach the goal.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:soul"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0002","text":"A perfect life is a contradiction in terms.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0003","text":"If I do an evil action, I must suffer for it; there is no power in this universe to stop or stay it.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:action"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0004","text":"After so much austerity I have known that the highest truth is this: He is present in every being! These are all in manifold forms of him. There is no other God to seek for! He alone is worshipping God, who serves all beings!","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:god","theme:truth"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0005","text":"Learn to recognise the mother in Evil, Terror, Sorrow, Denial, as well as in Sweetness and in Joy.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0006","text":"In spirituality the Americans are very inferior to us. But their society is very superior to ours","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0007","text":"India is immortal if she persists in her search for God. But if she goes in for politics and social conflict, she will die.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:god"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0008","text":"It is here that Indians build temples for Mohammedans and Christians; nowhere else. If you go to other countries and ask Mohammedans or people of other religions to build a temple for you, see how they will help. They will instead try to break down your temple and you too, if they can.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0009","text":"If all India stands up and takes all the mud that is at the bottom of the Indian Ocean and throws it up against the Western countries, it will not be doing an infinitesimal part of that which you are doing to us.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0010","text":"The greatest error is to call a man a weak and miserable sinner. Every time a person thinks in this mistaken manner, he rivets one more link in the chain of avidya that binds him, adds one more layer to the “self-hypnotism” that lies heavy over his mind.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:mind"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0011","text":"“One of the chief distinctions between the Vedic and the Christian religion is that the Christian religion teaches that each human soul had its beginning at its birth into this world, whereas the Vedic religion asserts that the spirit of man is an emanation of the Eternal Being and has no more a beginning than God Himself.”","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:soul","theme:god"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0012","text":"“Ye are the children of God, the sharers of immortal bliss, holy and perfect beings. Ye divinities on earth - sinners! It is a sin to call man so; it is a standing libel on human nature. Come up, lions! and shake off the delusion that you are sheep; you are souls immortal, spirits free, blest and eternal.”","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:soul","theme:god"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0013","text":"He is an atheist who does not believe in himself. The old religions said that he was an atheist who did not believe in God. The new religion says that he is an atheist who does not believe in himself.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:god"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0014","text":"Faith, faith, faith in ourselves, faith, faith in God, this is the secret of greatness. If you have faith in all the three hundred and thirty millions of your mythological Gods, and in all the Gods which foreigners have now and again introduced into your midst, and still have no faith in yourselves, there is no salvation for you.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:god"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0015","text":"The remedy for weakness is not brooding over weakness, but thinking of strength. Teach men of strength that is already within them.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:strength"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0016","text":"Death is better than a vegetating ignorant life; it is better to die on the battle-field than to live a life of defeat.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0017","text":"This world is the great gymnasium where we come to make ourselves strong.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0018","text":"It is the coward and the fool who says, This is my fate – so says the Sanskrit proverb. But it is the strong man who stands up and says, I will make my own fate. It is people who are getting old who talk of fate. Young men generally do not come to astrology.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0019","text":"Buddha is the only prophet who said, I do not care to know your various theories about God. What is the use of discussing all the subtle doctrines about the soul? Do good and be good.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:soul","theme:god"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0020","text":"This is the gist of all worship — to be pure and to do good to others. He who sees Shiva in the poor, in the weak, and in the diseased, really worships Shiva; and if he sees Shiva only in the image, his worship is but preliminary. He who has served and helped one poor man seeing Shiva in him, without thinking of his caste, or creed, or race, or anything, with him Shiva is more pleased than with the man who sees Him only in temples.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0021","text":"Arise, awake and Stop not till the Goal is Reached.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0022","text":"Let positive, strong, helpful thoughts enter into your brains from very childhood. Lay yourselves open to these thoughts, and not to weakening and paralysing ones.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0023","text":"Never mind failures; they are quite natural, they are the beauty of life, these failures. What would life be without them? It would not be worth having if it were not for struggles. Where would be the poetry of life? Never mind the struggles, the mistakes. I never heard a cow tell a lie, but it is only a cow—never a man. So never mind these failures, these little backslidings; hold the ideal a thousand times, and if you fail a thousand times, make the attempt once more.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:mind"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0024","text":"Say, ‘This misery that I am suffering is of my own doing, and that very thing proves that it will have to be undone by me alone.’ That which I created, I can demolish; that which is created by someone else, I shall never be able to destroy. Therefore, stand up, be bold, be strong. Take the whole responsibility on your own shoulders, and know that you are the creators of your own destiny. All the strength and success you want is within ourselves.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:strength"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0025","text":"We must overcome difficulty by constant practice. We must learn that nothing can happen to us unless we make ourselves susceptible to it.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0026","text":"Take up an idea, devote yourself to it, struggle on in patience, and the sun will rise for you.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0027","text":"Education is the manifestation of perfection present already in man. Religion is the manifestation of the divinity already in man.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0028","text":"Give me few men and women who are pure and selfless and I shall shake the world.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0029","text":"Strength is Life, Weakness is death.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:strength"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0030","text":"Condemn none: if you can stretch out a helping hand, do so. If you cannot, fold your hands, bless your brothers, and let them go their own way.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0031","text":"This life is short, the vanities of the world are transient, but they alone live who live for others, the rest are more dead than alive.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0032","text":"You cannot believe in God until you believe in yourself.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:god"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0033","text":"When we really begin to live in the world, then we understand what is meant by brotherhood or mankind, and not before.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0034","text":"External nature is only internal nature writ large.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0035","text":"The world is the great gymnasium where we come to make ourselves strong.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0036","text":"Feel like Christ and you will be a Christ; feel like Buddha and you will be a Buddha. It is feeling that is the life, the strength, the vitality, without which no amount of intellectual activity can reach God.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:god","theme:strength"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0037","text":"The will is not free—it is a phenomenon bound by cause and effect—but there is something behind the will which is free.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0038","text":"The more we come out and do good to others, the more our hearts will be purified, and God will be in them.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:god"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0039","text":"There is nothing beyond God, and the sense enjoyments are simply something through which we are passing now in the hope of getting better things.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:god"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0040","text":"The moment I have realized God sitting in the temple of every human body, the moment I stand in reverence before every human being and see God in him — that moment I am free from bondage, everything that binds vanishes, and I am free.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:god"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0041","text":"Our duty is to encourage every one in his struggle to live up to his own highest idea, and strive at the same time to make the ideal as near as possible to the Truth.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:truth","theme:duty"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0042","text":"That man has reached immortality who is disturbed by nothing material.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0043","text":"You have to grow from the inside out. None can teach you, none can make you spiritual. There is no other teacher but your own soul.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:soul"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0044","text":"The goal of mankind is knowledge. . . . Now this knowledge is inherent in man. No knowledge comes from outside: it is all inside. What we say a man \"knows,\" should, in strict psychological language, be what he \"discovers\" or \"unveils\"; what man \"learns\" is really what he discovers by taking the cover off his own soul, which is a mine of infinite knowledge.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:soul","theme:knowledge"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0045","text":"If money help a man to do good to others, it is of some value; but if not, it is simply a mass of evil, and the sooner it is got rid of, the better.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0046","text":"All differences in this world are of degree, and not of kind, because oneness is the secret of everything.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0047","text":"To devote your life to the good of all and to the happiness of all is religion. Whatever you do for your own sake is not religion.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0048","text":"The greatest religion is to be true to your own nature. Have faith in yourselves!","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0049","text":"The spirit is the cause of all our thoughts and body-action, and everything, but it is untouched by good or evil, pleasure or pain, heat or cold, and all the dualism of nature, although it lends its light to everything.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:action"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0050","text":"It is our own mental attitude which makes the world what it is for us. Our thought make things beautiful, our thoughts make things ugly. The whole world is in our own minds. Learn to see things in the proper light. First, believe in this world — that there is meaning behind everything. Everything in the world is good, is holy and beautiful. If you see something evil, think that you are not understanding it in the right light. throw the burden on yourselves!","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:mind"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0051","text":"In one word, this ideal is that you are divine.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0052","text":"All the powers in the universe are already ours. It is we who have put our hands before our eyes and cry that it is dark.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0053","text":"If faith in ourselves had been more extensively taught and practiced, I am sure a very large portion of the evils and miseries that we have would have vanished.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0054","text":"Where can we go to find God if we cannot see Him in our own hearts and in every living being?","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:god"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0055","text":"The Vedanta teaches that Nirvana can be attained here and now, that we do not have to wait for death to reach it. Nirvana is the realization of the Self; and after having once known that, if only for an instant, never again can one be deluded by the mirage of personality.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0056","text":"The Vedanta recognizes no sin it only recognizes error. And the greatest error, says the Vedanta is to say that you are weak, that you are a sinner, a miserable creature, and that you have no power and you cannot do this and that.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0057","text":"Never think there is anything impossible for the soul. It is the greatest heresy to think so. If there is sin, this is the only sin — to say that you are weak, or others are weak.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:soul"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0058","text":"Truth can be stated in a thousand different ways, yet each one can be true.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:truth"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0059","text":"\"I am the thread that runs through all these pearls,\" and each pearl is a religion or even a sect thereof. Such are the different pearls, and God is the thread that runs through all of them; most people, however, are entirely unconscious of it.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:god"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0060","text":"“Comfort” is no test of truth; on the contrary, truth is often far from being “comfortable.”","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:truth"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0061","text":"“Face the brutes.” That is a lesson for all life — face the terrible, face it boldly. Like the monkeys, the hardships of life fall back when we cease to flee before them.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0062","text":"A few heart-whole, sincere, and energetic men and women can do more in a year than a mob in a century.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0063","text":"A tremendous stream is flowing toward the ocean, carrying us all along with it; and though like straws and scraps of paper we may at times float aimlessly about, in the long run we are sure to join the Ocean of Life and Bliss.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0064","text":"All is the Self or Brahman. The saint, the sinner, the lamb, the tiger, even the murderer, as far as they have any reality, can be nothing else, because there is nothing else.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0065","text":"All knowledge that the world has ever received comes from the mind; the infinite library of the universe is in our own mind.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:mind","theme:knowledge"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0066","text":"All that is real in me is God; all that is real in God is I. The gulf between God and me is thus bridged. Thus by knowing God, we find that the kingdom of heaven is within us.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:god"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0067","text":"All truth is eternal. Truth is nobody’s property; no race, no individual can lay any exclusive claim to it. Truth is the nature of all souls.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:soul","theme:truth"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0068","text":"All who have actually attained any real religious experience never wrangle over the form in which the different religions are expressed. They know that the soul of all religions is the same and so they have no quarrel with anybody just because he or she does not speak in the same tongue.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:soul"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0069","text":"Anything that brings spiritual, mental, or physical weakness, touch it not with the toes of your feet.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0070","text":"Anything that is secret and mysterious in these systems of yoga should be at once rejected. The best guide in life is strength. In religion, as in all other matters, discard everything that weakens you, have nothing to do with it.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:yoga","theme:strength"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0071","text":"Are great things ever done smoothly? Time, patience, and indomitable will must show.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0072","text":"Are you unselfish? That is the question. If you are, you will be perfect without reading a single religious book, without going into a single church or temple.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0073","text":"As body, mind, or soul, you are a dream; you really are Being, Consciousness, Bliss (satchidananda). You are the God of this universe.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:mind","theme:soul","theme:god"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0074","text":"As long as we believe ourselves to be even the least different from God, fear remains with us; but when we know ourselves to be the One, fear goes; of what can we be afraid?","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:god","theme:courage"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0075","text":"As soon as I think that I am a little body, I want to preserve it, to protect it, to keep it nice, at the expense of other bodies; then you and I become separate.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0076","text":"As soon as you know the voice and understand what it is, the whole scene changes. The same world which was the ghastly battlefield of maya is now changed into something good and beautiful.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0077","text":"Astrology and all these mystical things are generally signs of a weak mind; therefore as soon as they are becoming prominent in our minds, we should see a physician, take good food, and rest.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:mind"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0078","text":"Be a hero. Always say, “I have no fear.” Tell this to everyone—“Have no fear.”","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:courage"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0079","text":"Be perfectly resigned, perfectly unconcerned; then alone can you do any true work. No eyes can see the real forces; we can only see the results. Put out self, forget it; just let God work, it is His business.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:god"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0080","text":"Blows are what awaken us and help to break the dream. They show us the insufficiency of this world and make us long to escape, to have freedom.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0081","text":"Both the forces of good and evil will keep the universe alive for us, until we awake from our dreams and give up this building of mud pies.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0082","text":"Come out into the broad light of day, come out from the little narrow paths, for how can the infinite soul rest content to live and die in small ruts?","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:soul"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0083","text":"Come out into the universe of Light. Everything in the universe is yours, stretch out your arms and embrace it with love. If you every felt you wanted to do that, you have felt God.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:god","theme:love"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0084","text":"Delusion will vanish as the light becomes more and more effulgent, load after load of ignorance will vanish, and then will come a time when all else has disappeared and the sun alone shines.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0085","text":"Desire, ignorance, and inequality—this is the trinity of bondage.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0086","text":"Despondency is not religion, whatever else it may be.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0087","text":"Do any deserve liberty who are not ready to give it to others? Let us calmly go to work, instead of dissipating our energy in unnecessary fretting and fuming.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0088","text":"Do not look back upon what has been done. Go ahead!","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0089","text":"Don't look back—forward, infinite energy, infinite enthusiasm, infinite daring, and infinite patience—then alone can great deeds be accomplished.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0090","text":"Each work has to pass through these stages—ridicule, opposition, and then acceptance. Those who think ahead of their time are sure to be misunderstood.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0091","text":"Even the greatest fool can accomplish a task if it were after his or her heart. But the intelligent ones are those who can convert every work into one that suits their taste.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0092","text":"Every action that helps us manifest our divine nature more and more is good; every action that retards it is evil.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:action"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0093","text":"Every individual is a center for the manifestation of a certain force. This force has been stored up as the resultant of our previous works, and each one of us is born with this force at our back.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0094","text":"Every step I take in light is mine forever.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0095","text":"Everything must be sacrificed, if necessary, for that one sentiment: universality.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0096","text":"Fear is death, fear is sin, fear is hell, fear is unrighteousness, fear is wrong life. All the negative thoughts and ideas that are in the world have proceeded from this evil spirit of fear.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:courage"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0097","text":"Fill the brain with high thoughts, highest ideals, place them day and night before you, and out of that will come great work.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0098","text":"First get rid of the delusion “I am the body,” then only will we want real knowledge.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:knowledge"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0099","text":"First, believe in the world—that there is meaning behind everything.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0100","text":"Freedom can never be reached by the weak. Throw away all weakness. Tell your body that it is strong, tell your mind that it is strong, and have unbounded faith and hope in yourself.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:mind"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0101","text":"Go on saying, “I am free.” Never mind if the next moment delusion comes and says, “I am bound.” Dehypnotize the whole thing.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:mind"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0102","text":"God is merciful to those whom He sees struggling heart and soul for realization. But remain idle, without any struggle, and you will see that His grace will never come.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:soul","theme:god"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0103","text":"God is self-evident, impersonal, omniscient, the Knower and the Master of nature, the Lord of all. He is behind all worship and it is being done according to Him, whether we know it or not.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:god"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0104","text":"God is very merciful to those whom He sees struggling heart and soul for spiritual realization. But remain idle, without any struggle, and you will see that His grace will never come.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:soul","theme:god"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0105","text":"Great work requires great and persistent effort for a long time. … Character has to be established through a thousand stumbles.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0106","text":"Have you got the will to surmount mountain-high obstructions? If the whole world stands against you sword in hand, would you still dare to do what you think is right?","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0107","text":"He whom the sages have been seeking in all these places is in our own hearts; the voice that you heard was right, says Vedanta, but the direction you gave to the voice was wrong.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0108","text":"Hold to the idea, “I am not the mind, I see that I am thinking, I am watching my mind act,” and each day the identification of yourself with thoughts and feelings will grow less, until at last you can entirely separate yourself from the mind and actually know it to be apart from yourself.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:mind"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0109","text":"However we may receive blows, and however knocked about we may be, the Soul is there and is never injured. We are that Infinite.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:soul"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0110","text":"I fervently wish no misery ever came near anyone; yet it is that alone that gives us an insight into the depths of our lives, does it not? In our moments of anguish, gates barred forever seem to open and let in many a flood of light.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0111","text":"I, for one, thoroughly believe that no power in the universe can withhold from anyone anything he really deserves.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0112","text":"If a piece of burning charcoal be placed on a man’s head, see how he struggles to throw it off. Similar will be the struggle for freedom of those who really understand that they are slaves of nature.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0113","text":"If superstition enters, the brain is gone.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0114","text":"If there is one word that you find coming out like a bomb from the Upanishads, bursting like a bombshell upon masses of ignorance, it is the word “fearlessness.”","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:courage"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0115","text":"If you think that you are bound, you remain bound; you make your own bondage. If you know that you are free, you are free this moment. This is knowledge, knowledge of freedom. Freedom is the goal of all nature.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:knowledge"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0116","text":"If you want to have life, you have to die every moment for it. Life and death are only different expressions of the same thing looked at from different standpoints; they are the falling and the rising of the same wave, and the two form one whole.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0117","text":"Impurity is a mere superimposition under which your real nature has become hidden. But the real you is already perfect, already strong.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0118","text":"Is there any sex-distinction in the Atman (Self)? Out with the differentiation between man and woman—all is Atman! Give up the identification with the body, and stand up!","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0119","text":"It is feeling that is the life, the strength, the vitality, without which no amount of intellectual activity can reach God.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:god","theme:strength"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0120","text":"It is the cheerful mind that is persevering. It is the strong mind that hews its way through a thousand difficulties.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:mind"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0121","text":"It is the patient building of character, the intense struggle to realize the truth, which alone will tell in the future of humanity.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:truth"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0122","text":"Karma is the eternal assertion of human freedom. If we can bring ourselves down by our karma, surely it is in our power to raise ourselves by our own karma.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0123","text":"Knowledge can only be got in one way, the way of experience; there is no other way to know.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:knowledge"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0124","text":"Learning and wisdom are superfluities, the surface glitter merely, but it is the heart that is the seat of all power.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0125","text":"Learning and wisdom are superfluities, the surface glitter merely, but it is the heart that is the seat of all power. It is not in the brain but in the heart that the Atman, possessed of knowledge, power, and activity, has its seat.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:knowledge"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0126","text":"Let us not depend upon the world for pleasure.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0127","text":"Let us worship the spirit in spirit, standing on spirit. Let the foundation be spirit, the middle spirit, the culmination spirit.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0128","text":"Look upon every man, woman, and everyone as God. You cannot help anyone, you can only serve: serve the children of the Lord, serve the Lord Himself, if you have the privilege.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:god"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0129","text":"Nature, body, mind go to death, not we. We neither go nor come. The man Vivekananda is in nature, is born and dies; but the Self we see as Vivekananda is never born and never dies. It is the eternal and unchangeable Reality.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:mind"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0130","text":"Neither seek nor avoid; take what comes. It is liberty to be affected by nothing. Do not merely endure; be unattached.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0131","text":"No authority can save us, no beliefs. If there is a God, all can find Him. No one needs to be told it is warm; all can discover it for themselves. So it should be with God. He should be a fact in the consciousness of every person.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:god"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0132","text":"One who leans on others cannot serve the God of Truth.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:god","theme:truth"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0133","text":"Our first duty is not to hate ourselves, because to advance we must have faith in ourselves first and then in God. Those who have no faith in themselves can never have faith in God.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:god","theme:duty"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0134","text":"Our supreme duty is to advance toward freedom—physical, mental, and spiritual—and help others to do so.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:duty"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0135","text":"Perfection does not come from belief or faith. Talk does not count for anything. Parrots can do that. Perfection comes through selfless work.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0136","text":"Perfection is always infinite. We are the Infinite already.You and I, and all beings, are trying to manifest that infinity.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0137","text":"Please everyone without becoming a hypocrite or a coward.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0138","text":"Pray all the time, read all the scriptures in the world, and worship all the gods there are ...but unless you realize the Truth, there is no freedom.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:god","theme:truth"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0139","text":"Pray all the time, read all the scriptures in the world, and worship all the gods there are …[but] unless you realize the Self (atman), there is no freedom.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:god"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0140","text":"Purity, patience, and perseverance are the three essentials to success and, above all, love.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:love"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0141","text":"Religion as a science, as a study, is the greatest and healthiest exercise that the human mind can have.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:mind"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0142","text":"Religion has no business to formulate social laws and insist on the difference between beings, because its aim and end is to obliterate all such fictions and monstrosities.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0143","text":"So long as there is desire or want, it is a sure sign that there is imperfection. A perfect, free being cannot have any desire.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0144","text":"Soft-brained people, weak-minded, chicken-hearted, cannot find the truth. One has to be free, and as broad as the sky.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:mind","theme:truth"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0145","text":"Stand as a rock; you are indestructible. You are the Self (atman), the God of the universe.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:god"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0146","text":"Stand up, be bold, be strong. Take the whole responsibility on your own shoulders, and know that you are the creator of your own destiny. All the strength and succor you want is within yourself. Therefore make your own future.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:strength"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0147","text":"Stand upon the Self, only then can we truly love the world. Take a very high stand; knowing our universal nature, we must look with perfect calmness upon all the panorama of the world.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:love"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0148","text":"Strength is the sign of vigor, the sign of life, the sign of hope, the sign of health, and the sign of everything that is good. As long as the body lives, there must be strength in the body, strength in the mind, strength in the hand.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:mind","theme:strength"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0149","text":"Superstition is our great enemy, but bigotry is worse.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0150","text":"Tell the truth boldly, whether it hurts or not. Never pander to weakness. If truth is too much for intelligent people and sweeps them away, let them go; the sooner the better.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:truth"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0151","text":"Thank God for giving you this world as a moral gymnasium to help your development, but never imagine you can help the world.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:god"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0152","text":"The essence of Vedanta is that there is but one Being and that every soul is that Being in full, not a part of that Being.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:soul"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0153","text":"The essential thing in religion is making the heart pure; the Kingdom of Heaven is within us, but only the pure in heart can see the King. While we think of the world, it is only the world for us; but let us come to it with the feeling that the world is God, and we shall have God.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:god"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0154","text":"The first sign that you are becoming religious is that you are becoming cheerful.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0155","text":"The human soul has sojourned in lower and higher forms, migrating from one to another according to the samskaras or impressions, but it is only in the highest form as a human being that it attains to freedom.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:soul"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0156","text":"The idea of perfect womanhood is perfect independence.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0157","text":"The important thing is: how much less you think of the body, of yourself as matter—as dead, dull, insentient matter; how much more you think of yourself as shining immortal being.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0158","text":"The less passion there is, the better we work. The calmer we are, the better for us and the more the amount of work we can do. When we let loose our feelings, we waste so much energy, shatter our nerves, disturb our minds, and accomplish very little work.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:mind"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0159","text":"The mind is but the subtle part of the body. You must retain great strength in your mind and words.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:mind","theme:strength"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0160","text":"The mistake is that we cling to the body when it is the spirit that is really immortal.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0161","text":"The more you think of yourself as shining immortal spirit, the more eager you will be to be absolutely free of matter, body, and senses. This is the intense desire to be free.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0162","text":"The past was great no doubt, but I sincerely believe that the future will be more glorious still.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0163","text":"The power is with the silent ones, who only live and love and then withdraw their personality. They never say “me” and “mine”; they are only blessed in being instruments.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:love"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0164","text":"The powers of the mind are like the rays of the sun when they are concentrated they illumine.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:mind"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0165","text":"The power of purity—it is a definite power.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0166","text":"The powers of the mind should be concentrated and the mind turned back upon itself; as the darkest places reveal their secrets before the penetrating rays of the sun, so will the concentrated mind penetrate its own innermost secrets.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:mind"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0167","text":"The Self when it appears behind the universe is called God. The same Self when it appears behind this little universe—the body—is the soul.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:soul","theme:god"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0168","text":"The Soul is not composed of any materials. It is unity indivisible. Therefore it must be indestructible.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:soul"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0169","text":"The varieties of religious belief are an advantage, since all faiths are good, so far as they encourage us to lead a religious life. The more sects there are, the more opportunities there are for making a successful appeal to the divine instinct in all of us.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0170","text":"The whole secret of existence is to have no fear. Never fear what will become of you, depend on no one. Only the moment you reject all help are you free.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:courage"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0171","text":"The whole universe is one. There is only one Self in the universe, only One Existence.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0172","text":"The world is ready to give up its secrets if we only know how to knock, how to give it the necessary blow. The strength and force of the blow come through concentration.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:strength"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0173","text":"There cannot be friendship without equality.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0174","text":"There is no help for you outside of yourself; you are the creator of the universe. Like the silkworm you have built a cocoon around yourself…. Burst your own cocoon and come out as the beautiful butterfly, as the free soul. Then alone you will see Truth.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:soul","theme:truth"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0175","text":"There is one thing to be remembered: that the assertion — I am God — cannot be made with regard to the sense-world.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:god"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0176","text":"There is only one sin. That is weakness.... The only saint is that soul that never weakens, faces everything, and determines to die game.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:soul"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0177","text":"There is to be found in every religion the manifestation of the struggle toward freedom. It is the groundwork of all morality, of unselfishness, which means getting rid of the idea that human beings are the same as this little body.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0178","text":"This earth is higher than all the heavens; this is the greatest school in the universe.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0179","text":"This I have seen in life—those who are overcautious about themselves fall into dangers at every step; those who are afraid of losing honor and respect, get only disgrace; and those who are always afraid of loss, always lose.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0180","text":"This is no world. It is God Himself. In delusion we call it world.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:god"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0181","text":"This is the first lesson to learn: be determined not to curse anything outside, not to lay the blame upon anyone outside, but stand up, lay the blame on yourself. You will find that is always true. Get hold of yourself.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0182","text":"This is the great lesson that we are here to learn through myriads of births and heavens and hells—that there is nothing to be asked for, desired for, beyond one’s spiritual Self (atman).","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0183","text":"This life is a hard fact; work your way through it boldly, though it may be adamantine; no matter, the soul is stronger.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:soul"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0184","text":"Those who grumble at the little thing that has fallen to their lot to do will grumble at everything. Always grumbling, they will lead a miserable life, and everything will be a failure. But those who do their duties as they go, putting their shoulders to the wheel, will see the light, and higher duties will fall to their share.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0185","text":"Those who work at a thing heart and soul not only achieve success in it but through their absorption in that they also realize the supreme truth—Brahman. Those who work at a thing with their whole heart receive help from God.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:soul","theme:god","theme:truth"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0186","text":"To believe blindly is to degenerate the human soul. Be an atheist if you want, but do not believe in anything unquestioningly.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:soul"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0187","text":"Truth does not pay homage to any society, ancient or modern. Society has to pay homage to Truth or die.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:truth"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0188","text":"Understanding human nature is the highest knowledge, and only by knowing it can we know God. It is also a fact that the knowledge of God is the highest knowledge, and only by knowing God can we understand human nature.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:knowledge","theme:god"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0189","text":"Unselfishness is God.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:god"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0190","text":"Watch people do their most common actions; these are indeed the things that will tell you the real character of a great person.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:action"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0191","text":"We are ever free if we would only believe it, only have faith enough. You are the soul, free and eternal, ever free, ever blessed. Have faith enough and you will be free in a minute.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:soul"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0192","text":"We believe that every being is divine, is God. Every soul is a sun covered over with clouds of ignorance; the difference between soul and soul is owing to the difference in density of these layers of clouds.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:soul","theme:god"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0193","text":"We came to enjoy; we are being enjoyed. We came to rule; we are being ruled. We came to work; we are being worked. All the time, we find that. And this comes into every detail of our life.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0194","text":"We have to go back to philosophy to treat things as they are. We are suffering from our own karma. It is not the fault of God. What we do is our own fault, nothing else. Why should God be blamed?","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:god"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0195","text":"We must approach religion with reverence and with love, and our heart will stand up and say, this is truth, and this is untruth.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:love","theme:truth"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0196","text":"We must be bright and cheerful. Long faces do not make religion. Religion should be the most joyful thing in the world, because it is the best.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0197","text":"We must have friendship for all; we must be merciful toward those that are in misery; when people are happy, we ought to be happy; and to the wicked we must be indifferent. These attitudes will make the mind peaceful.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:mind"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0198","text":"We reap what we sow. We are the makers of our own fate. None else has the blame, none has the praise.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0199","text":"We want to know in order to make ourselves free. That is our life: one universal cry for freedom.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0200","text":"What do you gain in heaven? You become gods, drink nectar, and get rheumatism. There is less misery there than on earth, but also less truth.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:god","theme:truth"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0201","text":"What the world wants is character. The world is in need of those whose life is one burning love, selfless. That love will make every word tell like a thunderbolt.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:love"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0202","text":"When we come to nonattachment, then we can understand the marvelous mystery of the universe: how it is intense activity and at the same time intense peace, how it is work every moment and rest every moment.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0203","text":"When we have become free, we need not go mad and throw up society and rush off to die in the forest or the cave; we shall remain where we were but we shall understand the whole thing. The same phenomena will remain but with a new meaning.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0204","text":"When we have become free, we need not go mad and throw up society and rush off to die in the forest or the cave; we shall remain where we were, only we shall understand the whole thing.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0205","text":"Whenever we attain a higher vision, the lower vision disappears of itself.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0206","text":"Who makes us ignorant? We ourselves. We put our hands over our eyes and weep that it is dark.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0207","text":"Why are people so afraid? The answer is that they have made themselves helpless and dependent on others. We are so lazy, we do not want to do anything ourselves. We want a Personal God, a Savior or a Prophet to do everything for us.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:god"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0208","text":"Woman has suffered for eons, and that has given her infinite patience and infinite perseverance.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0209","text":"Women will work out their destinies — much better, too, than men can ever do for them. All the mischief to women has come because men undertook to shape the destiny of women.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0210","text":"Work and worship are necessary to take away the veil, to lift off the bondage and illusion.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0211","text":"Work on with the intrepidity of a lion but at the same time with the tenderness of a flower.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0212","text":"Worship of society and popular opinion is idolatry. The soul has no sex, no country, no place, no time.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:soul"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0213","text":"What makes you weep, my friend? In you is all power. Summon up your all-powerful nature, O mighty one, and this whole universe will lie at your feet. It is the Self alone that predominates, and not matter.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0214","text":"Great undertakings are always fraught with many obstacles. It is these obstacles which knock and shape great characters.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0215","text":"In every attempt there will be one set of men who will applaud, and another who will pick holes. Go on doing your own work, what need have you to reply to any party?","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0216","text":"Come up, O lions, and shake off the delusion that you are sheep; you are souls immortal, spirits free, blest and eternal; ye are not matter, ye are not bodies; matter is your servant, not you the servant of matter.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:soul"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0217","text":"You are such a big receptacle... I thought you were like a huge banyan-tree and would give shelter to thousands of weary souls.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:soul"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0218","text":"Vivekananda often asserted that only in becoming a ṛṣi does one understand the scripture properly. His argument appears to be that as products and records of direct perception, these texts were not written for the intellect, or for understanding through a process of rational inquiry and analysis. They become meaningful only when one has lifted oneself to the same heights of perception.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0219","text":"“The bird of the spirit of Humanity cannot fly with only one wing” —these are words of Vivekananda, who meant to affirm the great significance of the Feminine Principle. Man does not willingly give full rights to woman. However, this opposition but intensifies the forces; and woman, fighting for her cosmic rights, will acquire the knowledge of her power. (LHR I, p 325) (10 September 1934)","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration","theme:knowledge"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0220","text":"If you want to know India study Vivekananda. In him everything is positive and nothing negative.","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0221","text":"Sister Nivedita (1867–1911), a disciple of Swami Vivekananda","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0222","text":"Quotes on Swami Vivekananda on reviving India","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0223","text":"Complete Works of Vivekananda, Belur Math publication","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0224","text":"Vivekananda Vedanta Network","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0225","text":"Quotes of Swami Vivekananda (with source citations)","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."},{"id":"vivekananda-0226","text":"quotes by Vivekananda","author":"Swami Vivekananda","source":"Swami Vivekananda","tags":["tradition:hindu","tradition:vedanta","language:en","theme:philosophy","theme:self","theme:spirituality","audience:inspiration"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified from English Wikiquote page."}]}